# Background and Asset Policy

Do not blindly use the reference screenshot as a full-screen background image.

The auth UI must be implemented as real frontend code.

## Required Question Before Background Implementation

Before implementing the background, ask the user:

> Should I recreate the background using CSS gradients, radial glows, blur and subtle effects, or should I use the reference as an image asset?

Recommend:

> I recommend recreating it through code for better responsiveness, maintainability and performance.

## Preferred Background Implementation

Use CSS-based background effects:

- linear gradients;
- radial gradients;
- blurred glow layers;
- pseudo-elements;
- subtle vignette;
- optional subtle grain/noise;
- optional tiny particles only if they do not distract.

## Allowed Image Usage

Image assets are allowed only for:

- logo if provided as SVG/PNG;
- decorative assets explicitly approved by the user;
- background image only if the user explicitly chooses image-based implementation.

## Do Not

- Do not place the entire reference image behind the UI.
- Do not make the page look correct only at one resolution.
- Do not use huge raster images when CSS can reproduce the effect.
- Do not add heavy animated background libraries.
- Do not make background effects interfere with readability.
